- Remove prisma db push --accept-data-loss from the automatic start
  command (server/start.sh, package.json). Schema changes now go through
  Prisma Migrate (db:deploy, wired as Railway preDeployCommand) instead of
  a live schema diff applied on every boot.
- Add server/scripts/generate-baseline-migration.sh + migration_lock.toml
  scaffold for the one-time baseline-migration cutover (documented in
  docs/product/CLOSED_BETA_GATE.md - could not be executed in this
  sandbox, no network access to binaries.prisma.sh).
- Harden GET /health/email: was checking only the Gmail-SMTP fallback
  vars (reporting misconfigured even with SendGrid correctly set) and
  leaking SMTP_HOST/SMTP_USER/EMAIL_FROM/CLIENT_URL plus 8 chars of
  SMTP_PASS with no auth. Now detects the real provider and returns
  presence booleans only.
- RegisterPage.jsx: replace the single bundled terms+age checkbox with
  four explicit, unchecked-by-default checkboxes (age/terms/privacy/
  sensitive-data). auth.ts registerSchema now hard-requires
  ageConfirmed/privacyAccepted/sensitiveDataAccepted === true instead of
  the BETA.2 soft optional-but-not-false check.
- Fix Active Profile Context bug: discovery.ts like/pass/block/report
  and matches.ts accept/reject used the direct Profile.userId relation
  instead of resolveMyProfileId, so a couple/group non-creator member
  got 404s and anyone with a switched active profile still acted as their
  individual profile. privacy.ts GET/PUT had the same bug.
- Add EligibilityService.forProfileContext(profileId, userId), wired into
  discovery.ts like/pass as an enforcement gate.
- Add npm run beta:gate (server/src/scripts/betaGate.ts) - schema/type/
  env/start-command/health-endpoint checks, never prints secret values.
- Add docs/product/CLOSED_BETA_GATE.md.

Validated in this sandbox: server tsc --noEmit (PASS, exit 0), client
vite build (PASS). npm test and prisma validate/generate could not run
here - binaries.prisma.sh is blocked by this sandbox's network allowlist
(confirmed via direct curl: 403 blocked-by-allowlist). GitHub Actions
already proves that domain is reachable in CI - run the suite there or
locally before merging.
